  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-24 + Q20 owner directive: author a binding regression test verifying that R6 FR-30 CapabilityRouter dedup semantics are preserved through the new dispatcher path after WP4 cutover. The dedup invariant: chat + workspace SUM-CHAT siblings (`summarize-document-for-chat` + `summarize-document-for-workspace`) dedup to ONE render — one Workspace tab + one chat ack — not two independent renders. Task 141's tool-filtering replacement must structurally preserve this; task 143 verifies.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF integration test engineer. Knows the R6 FR-30 dedup behavior.</role>

  <goal>
    Integration test exists asserting: when user invokes the SUM-CHAT capability (chat + workspace siblings), the new dispatcher routes to ONE playbook + emits ONE Workspace tab open + ONE chat ack — NOT two. Test fails if WP4 cutover regressed dedup. Marked binding-invariant.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-24 + Q20 + design §WP4 phased removal "preserve dedup semantics through the new dispatcher". The R6 FR-30 dedup test suite passed under the old CapabilityRouter + PlaybookDispatcher dual-layer architecture. After task 141 deletes CapabilityRouter, dedup must remain structurally enforced through `PlaybookDispatcher` + the new tool-filtering replacement + `DispatchResult.NodeDestination` (from WP3 Phase 3). This test asserts the invariant.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Services/Ai/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookDispatcher.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOutputHandler.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-24 acceptance — existing dedup test suite remains green; one Workspace tab + one chat ack for `summarize-document-for-workspace` invocation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="owner-clarification">Q20 — preserve CapabilityRouter dedup semantics in new PlaybookDispatcher path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Test fixtures tier-1 safe — synthetic documents only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test marked with binding-invariant trait — fails loudly on regression.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
