  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Locate any existing R6 FR-30 dedup tests in `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/` (likely under `Services/Ai/Capabilities/` or `Services/Ai/Routing/`). Catalog and decide: migrate to new dispatcher fixtures vs replace.</step>
    <step order="2">Author new integration test "SumChatSiblings_DedupToOneRender": (a) invoke chat-Summarize with `summarize-document-for-workspace`; (b) assert exactly ONE Workspace tab open event + ONE chat ack message; (c) assert PlaybookDispatcher selected one playbook (not two).</step>
    <step order="3">Add a deliberate negative-control sub-test: a turn that DOES produce two distinct renders (e.g., a multi-node playbook with both Workspace + Chat outputs) — verify that case is NOT incorrectly deduped.</step>
    <step order="4">Mark with binding-invariant trait / category.</step>
    <step order="5">Run `dotnet test`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="6">Sanity-check: temporarily disable dedup in dispatcher; verify test FAILS (confirms the gate has teeth). Restore.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 143 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Existing dedup tests + PlaybookDispatcher.cs</tool>
    <tool name="Write">New integration test</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet test</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Services/Ai/Routing/SumChatDedupPreservationTests.cs (or equivalent path)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Test asserts exactly ONE Workspace tab + ONE chat ack for SUM-CHAT sibling invocation.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Negative-control sub-test passes (legitimate multi-render case NOT deduped).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Test passes against current (post-task-141, post-task-142) state.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Test marked binding-invariant.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Sanity-check confirms test FAILS if dedup artificially disabled.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The R6 FR-30 dedup invariant is sacred — it's what users see (no duplicate tab + chat ack stutter). This test is the safety net for any future dispatcher refactor.
  </notes>

